    <item>
      <title>Tank&amp;#039;s Birthday - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/</guid>
      <pubDate>Wed, 07 May 2025 23:15:29 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8111" class="post-8111 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Tank&amp;#8217;s Birthday&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Truffles was talking about how cute she looked in her diamond shirt. She even (falsely) claimed that she spent a fortune on it! 😮&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Truffles: I know that! After all, I spent a fortune on it, on my Wii!" class="wp-image-8113" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;That&amp;#8217;s hogwash!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I know it&amp;#8217;s not true because I bought it for her &lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/02/28/impossible-request/"&gt;myself&lt;/a&gt;! Whatever &amp;#8220;fortune&amp;#8221; she&amp;#8217;s talking about must be a &lt;em&gt;pig-ment&lt;/em&gt; of her imagination.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was Tank&amp;#8217;s birthday, so I headed over to his party.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Tank: YESSS! That thing in your pocket! That's my present, right, snappy?" class="wp-image-8114" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I gave him a Moai statue that I got from Gulliver a while back. (I&amp;#8217;ve been keeping a couple furniture items in my pockets for situations like this.) He seemed to enjoy the gift, and he gave me a black bishop in return. He even said now we&amp;#8217;re best friends until the end of the universe!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Tank: As of now, we're best buds until the end of the universe, snappy!" class="wp-image-8115" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Soo&amp;#8230;until Tuesday or so?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline was also at Tank&amp;#8217;s party, and she had an interesting idiom about cake. Too bad this game doesn&amp;#8217;t even have cake at birthday parties. 😛🎂&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Caroline: There's nothing better than birthday cake. It's like a slice of concentrated love." class="wp-image-8116" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Drift was talking about how seeing the frothy sea makes him want to catch some huge fish.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Drift: Looking at the frothy sea makes me wanna grab a ship and catch something huge!" class="wp-image-8117" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Okay, but how exactly are you going to grab a ship?&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;He said it would be a &amp;#8220;hot adventure&amp;#8221; of fish vs. abs. Drift is a weird dude.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Drift: Whoa, yeah! HOT ADVENTURE! Fish vs. abs, in a pond!" class="wp-image-8118" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Whitney seemed really excited about the bear shirt that I gave her last week. It&amp;#8217;s nice to see them follow up about things like this. I&amp;#8217;m glad she likes it so much! 😊&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array" alt="Whitney: Wow, it's been a while since I've word something that makes me THIS pretty!" class="wp-image-8119" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I could only find one of today&amp;#8217;s fossils, despite taking an extra walk around town specifically looking for them! I&amp;#8217;ll have to try again (and look harder) next time. 😛&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/07/tanks-birthday/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-05-07T19:15:29-04:00"&gt;May 7, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-05-07T19:16:39-04:00"&gt;May 7, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/truffles-fortune.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Rain, Rosie, Rugs - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 04 May 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13380" class="post-13380 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Rain, Rosie, Rugs&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;It was a rainy day in town today, and most of my villagers were complaining about it. Monty, though, complained that I looked happy despite the rain.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/Array" alt="Monty: How can you look so happy in this nasty weather? Yup... I always knew you were a strange one." class="wp-image-13381" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I found a new house near my northwest bridge. (It&amp;#8217;s not the spot where Tom lived, but it&amp;#8217;s just a bit south of there.) That means that Ed&amp;#8217;s replacement has moved in, so I quickly went inside. I was quite happy to meet my newest neighbor!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/Array" alt="Rosie: Well, I'm Rosie, and I'm the newest resident of your awesome town!" class="wp-image-13382" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It&amp;#8217;s Rosie the cat! She lived in Forest back in 2011, but I also had her in Wild World from 2018-2020. I like her a lot, so I&amp;#8217;m glad to have her around once again! 🙂&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Big Top asked me to make a delivery to Mint, and I agreed to help out. The gift was a cabin rug, and I didn&amp;#8217;t think much of it at first.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/Array" alt="Mint: Oh! It's a cabin rug!" class="wp-image-13384" sizes="(max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I returned to Big Top, however, I had to do a double take. His reward for me was &lt;strong&gt;also &lt;/strong&gt;a cabin rug!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="499" height="280" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/Array" alt="Big Top: Oh, that's right... to thank you, I want to give you a cabin rug!" class="wp-image-13385" sizes="auto, (max-width: 499px) 100vw, 499px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;How many cabin rugs does this guy have? 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Over at town hall, I found two furniture items in the recycle bin this afternoon: a deluxe range and a pine chair.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I played again this evening, mainly to check out K.K. Slider&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show at the Roost. I asked for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Calypso&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Calypso." class="wp-image-13386" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;K.K. looked tired or something in this screenshot. 😪&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;After the show, I decided to shake some trees. I found both of today&amp;#8217;s furniture items: a wheat field and a blue wardrobe. But more importantly, I encountered five bees and I caught them all! Going 5-for-5 is &lt;em&gt;very &lt;/em&gt;unusual for me in this game, but I felt like a pro, for the day at least. 😆🐝&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/Array" alt="I caught a bee! Bzz! Bzz! Bzz!" class="wp-image-13387" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/05/03/rain-rosie-rugs/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-05-03T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;May 3, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-05-04T00:17:28-04:00"&gt;May 4, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/RUU_8223-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Eight Sizes Too Small - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Horizons Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 04 May 2025 02:43:37 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8741" class="post-8741 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Eight Sizes Too Small&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Monday, I got to see the inside of Peanut&amp;#8217;s house for the first time since she unpacked. She has a lot of pink cute furniture in her house, which reminds me of the lovely furniture in the older games.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="The inside of Peanut's house. How cute!" class="wp-image-8743" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Ankha&amp;#8217;s catchphrase continues to pay dividends. She told me that the Nooklings are so cute, she can&amp;#8217;t resist buying their items&amp;#8230;before adding that she hates it. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="Ankha: When they recommend an item with those adorable smiles, I can't possibly say no, I hate it." class="wp-image-8744" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;On Tuesday, Drago the &lt;s&gt;dragon&lt;/s&gt; gator was camping at the campsite. I like Drago, and I&amp;#8217;ve had him in New Leaf many years ago. But I did not invite him to move in.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="Drago: I'm on a camping trip, trying to meet good food." class="wp-image-8745" sizes="(max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Please don&amp;#8217;t eat me. I taste terrible.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I visited Merengue on Wednesday, she told me I looked great in my striped shirt. She told me some striped socks would go great with it, so she gave me some. For once, one of these gifts actually made sense (stripes with stripes). Usually, they&amp;#8217;re unrelated and don&amp;#8217;t match.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="Merengue: You deserve nice things, a bit." class="wp-image-8746" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Louie was checking out a henley shirt at Able Sisters. However, I don&amp;#8217;t think it would quite fit him. It&amp;#8217;s about eight sizes too small. 👕&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="Louie sizes up a henley shirt. I think it's too small for him." class="wp-image-8747" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;For a Donkey Kong-sized gorilla to fit into that shirt, it would take quite a &lt;em&gt;Tropical Squeeze&lt;/em&gt;. 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Today, Ankha told me that she decides what to make for dinner based on the weather. She said that creamed spinach was on the menu today. It was a sunny day, though. Creamed spinach seems more like a rainy/cloudy day meal to me. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="Ankha: Today's weather leaves me feeling like, let's see...creamed spinach!" class="wp-image-8749" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;And of course, she added in her catchphrase. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="700" height="394" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/Array" alt="Ankha: I'm hungry already, I hate it!" class="wp-image-8748" sizes="auto, (max-width: 700px) 100vw, 700px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;On Wednesday, I sold 18 bugs to Flick for 86,250 bells.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I helped out Gulliver on Thursday, and he sent me another candy-skull mask.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;I shot down a balloon present today, and I found a milk-glass lamp inside.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Tonight, K.K. Slider performed &amp;#8220;I Love You&amp;#8221; for me, Louie, and Ankha.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I posted my latest New Horizons Moments video the other day, so I hope you&amp;#8217;ll check it out if you haven&amp;#8217;t seen it yet:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;figure class="wp-block-embed is-type-video is-provider-youtube wp-block-embed-youtube wp-embed-aspect-16-9 wp-has-aspect-ratio"&gt;&lt;div class="wp-block-embed__wrapper"&gt; &lt;iframe loading="lazy" title="New Horizons Moments #33 (Animal Crossing)" width="660" height="371" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/vg0kbtAn_uQ?feature=oembed" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen&gt;&lt;/iframe&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;/figure&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/2025/05/03/eight-sizes-too-small/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-05-03T22:43:37-04:00"&gt;May 3, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-05-03T22:45:24-04:00"&gt;May 3, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acnhblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/peanut-house-sm.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Doing Favors - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACWW Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sat, 03 May 2025 02:23:33 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-8099" class="post-8099 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Doing Favors&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	 	 	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Wednesday, Robin told me she&amp;#8217;s been collecting blue furniture lately.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="Robin: Lately I've been collecting blue furniture." class="wp-image-8100" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I took a look in the shop, and they had an elephant slide, which is partially blue. I bought it and took it over to Robin, and she said she didn&amp;#8217;t even remember asking me for blue furniture! Even though &lt;em&gt;only three minutes&lt;/em&gt; had passed! 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="Robin: I haven't even mentioned blue furniture to you!" class="wp-image-8101" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;What a birdbrain.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;But still, she accepted the gift. She rewarded me with some checkered tile.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday was the start of May, so I received my monthly bank statement in the mail. I earned 76,900 bells in interest this month.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Saharah was in town, and she again lost all her addresses.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="Saharah: All my addresses...gone! My deliveries! My customers! What is a camel to do?!" class="wp-image-8102" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I helped her out by taking a rug to Mabel, some wallpaper to Pelly (for Phyllis), and some wallpaper to Blathers. In return, Saharah offered me a concrete floor. That&amp;#8217;s a solid reward, and it&amp;#8217;s a good way to cement our friendship. 😉&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Flea Market day is coming up on Saturday, and Truffles was looking forward to it. Except that she had a different name for it: Sell-Your-Lame-Old-Junk Day. 😆&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="Truffles: Hey, Sell-Your-Lame-Old-Junk day is on Saturday, on my Wii!" class="wp-image-8103" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Caroline asked me to deliver a gift to Tank today, and it was a Nile shirt. He said it was &amp;#8220;great,&amp;#8221; but he followed that up with &amp;#8220;I guess.&amp;#8221; So it didn&amp;#8217;t exactly sound convincing. Or maybe he was in &lt;em&gt;de Nile&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="Tank: Great, I guess, snappy." class="wp-image-8104" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I returned to Caroline and told her I made the delivery. She asked what Tank thought of it, and I said it was awesome. I didn&amp;#8217;t tell her about the &amp;#8220;I guess&amp;#8221; remark. 😛&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="&amp;gt;It was AWESOME!" class="wp-image-8105" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She then rewarded me with 510 bells.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Whitney asked me for some new clothes, so I bought her a bear shirt at Able Sisters. It may not be flashy, but it&amp;#8217;s good for when she just wants the &lt;em&gt;bear &lt;/em&gt;essentials.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="299" src="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array" alt="Whitney: What?! Did you say you were going to give me this bear shirt?" class="wp-image-8106" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 85vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She rewarded me with a pink tartan. I wonder why she didn&amp;#8217;t just wear &lt;em&gt;this &lt;/em&gt;instead of asking me for clothes? 😛&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Here are a few other quick notes about this week:&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;ul class="wp-block-list"&gt; &lt;li&gt;I shot down a yellow balloon present yesterday, and I found an automatic washer inside.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Curt came down with a cold this week, so I gave him some medicine yesterday and today.&lt;/li&gt;    &lt;li&gt;Over at town hall, I found a classic buffet in the recycle bin. I guess it was a &lt;em&gt;leftover &lt;/em&gt;from a feast that didn&amp;#8217;t &lt;em&gt;pan &lt;/em&gt;out.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;img alt='' src='https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/Array' class='avatar avatar-49 photo' height='49' width='49'/&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/2025/05/02/doing-favors/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-05-02T22:23:33-04:00"&gt;May 2, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-05-02T22:34:48-04:00"&gt;May 2, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt; &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/acwwblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/05/robin-blue1.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Multi-Camper Week - Jeff&amp;#039;s New Leaf Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/</guid>
      <pubDate>Thu, 01 May 2025 03:57:21 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-18197" class="post-18197 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Multi-Camper Week&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;On Sunday, Lionel was camping at the campsite. He told me he&amp;#8217;s not anyone suspicious, but I think he&amp;#8217;s &lt;em&gt;lion&lt;/em&gt; to me. 😉&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Lionel, at the campsite: Oh, I'm not anyone suspicious!" class="wp-image-18199" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monday night, the manhole entrance to Resetti&amp;#8217;s surveillance center was open.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="An open manhole marking the entrance to the Reset Center." class="wp-image-18200" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I dropped in for a visit, but Resetti wasn&amp;#8217;t in a very friendly mood. (Is he ever?)&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Resetti: You ain't gonna find nothin', so quit snoopin' around!" class="wp-image-18201" sizes="(max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Hornsby asked me to catch a pill bug for him, and I agreed to help out. It only took me a minute or two to find one, and I caught it not far from Hornsby. You can even see him in the background of this screenshot.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="I caught a pill bug! I don't know... It seems nice to me! 11.8mm" class="wp-image-18202" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;When I took it over to him, he rewarded me with a bubble tee. He said he hoped that I liked it, but I didn&amp;#8217;t tell him what I &lt;em&gt;really &lt;/em&gt;thought of the gift. I didn&amp;#8217;t want to burst his bubble. 🫧&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Yesterday, Lucky the dog/mummy was camping at the campsite. I &lt;em&gt;really &lt;/em&gt;wish I had a spot for him!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Lucky: I'm here camping in town, so you'll be seeing me around for a bit!" class="wp-image-18203" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;This one really stings.&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I had a chat with Mira near the illuminated arch, and the arch didn&amp;#8217;t disappear when I started the conversation. So it blocked my view of Mira as she told me about a book she read. It was called &lt;em&gt;Rabbit Storm Caller&lt;/em&gt;, and she wondered if she might have storm-calling superpowers too.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Mira: I wonder if I have storm-calling superpowers?" class="wp-image-18204" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;figcaption class="wp-element-caption"&gt;Go on, give it a try! Hop to it!&lt;/figcaption&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, Mira offered me a free BB tee. I accepted it, and I decided to put it on.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;I had yet another camper today. In fact, &lt;em&gt;two &lt;/em&gt;of them!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Marcie: I might not be here long, but I hope we get to know each other." class="wp-image-18205" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;It was Marcie the kangaroo, and her joey. 😛 I had no interest in adopting them, even if I could. &lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Aurora asked me for something to replace her pill bug. The best I could come up with was a baseball set that I bought at Harv&amp;#8217;s campground. It is baseball season now, after all. To my surprise, Aurora thought it was a home run. ⚾&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Aurora: Oh! A baseball set is exactly what I needed!" class="wp-image-18206" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Unfortunately, she struck out on the reward: She just gave me the pill bug. 😛 &lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="Aurora: Oh! In exchange, let me give you the pill bug I was using." class="wp-image-18207" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I later released it back into the wild (because my pockets filled up). 😆&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;A bit later, I spotted a balloon present soaring high in the air&amp;#8230;and I shot it down.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="400" height="240" src="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/Array" alt="A balloon present falls to the ground after its balloon is popped." class="wp-image-18208" sizes="auto, (max-width: 400px) 100vw, 400px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;There was a laptop inside, so I guess this serves as my introduction to cloud computing. 😉 ☁️&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Have a great day (or night), and I hope to see you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/2025/04/30/multi-camper-week/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-04-30T23:57:21-04:00"&gt;April 30, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-05-01T00:07:22-04:00"&gt;May 1, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
      <media:content url="https://www.jvgs.net/newleafblog/wp-content/uploads/2025/04/20250427_HNI_0018.jpg" type="image/jpeg"/>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Marina&amp;#039;s Squid - Jeff&amp;#039;s ACCF Blog</title>
      <author>Jeff</author>
      <link>https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/</link>
      <guid isPermaLink="true">https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/</guid>
      <pubDate>Sun, 27 Apr 2025 03:58:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <description>&lt;article id="post-13367" class="post-13367 post type-post status-publish format-standard hentry category-uncategorized"&gt; 	 	&lt;header class="entry-header"&gt; 		&lt;h1 class="entry-title"&gt;Marina&amp;#8217;s Squid&lt;/h1&gt;	&lt;/header&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-header --&gt;  	&lt;div class="entry-content"&gt; 		 &lt;p&gt;I played on Sunday, and I received a cute letter from Mint in the mail. It was about the game of hide-and-seek that we played last week.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img fetchpriority="high" width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="To Jeff, Thanks for playing hide-and-seek with us earlier. It's nice to just play like a kid sometimes, isn't it? -From: Mint" class="wp-image-13368" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She sent me a metal guitar as my prize for winning the game.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;It was Easter Sunday (aka Bunny Day), so I had a chat with the one-and-only Zipper T. Bunny.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Zipper: boingity boing! Hello there!" class="wp-image-13369" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;I dug up all the bunny eggs I could find. Some had candy inside, and others had bunny foils. I found 11 of the 12 bunny foils, and I redeemed them for egg furniture. (I didn&amp;#8217;t worry about the one I missed.) I sold the 11 items for a total of 98,888 bells. 💰&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;But Antonio was more concerned with the rain, and the mud it was creating. He apparently wanted to wrestle someone in the mud!&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Antonio: It's getting nice and muddy around here! Now, if someone would volunteer to let me tackle them in it..." class="wp-image-13370" sizes="(max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Today, I received a goodbye letter in the mail from the horse that recently depart-&lt;em&gt;Ed&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Yo, Jeff, This is it, my last day in Forest! Living here made me realize just how burly I really am. Tell everyone thanks for being so scrawny!" class="wp-image-13371" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Robin was feeling sick&amp;#8230;and unpretty. I gave her a dose of medicine to help with the cold. As for being unpretty, she&amp;#8217;s on her own there.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Robin: P-p-please. never felt so... unpretty. Qu-qu-quickly..." class="wp-image-13372" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Monty told me that he recently visited Nana, and he said she&amp;#8217;s quite a good cook! He particularly loved the garlic bread that was drowned in green onion(s)? I&amp;#8217;m not sure about the onions, but whatever floats your garlic bread, man.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Monty: The garlic bread I had was just drowned in green onion. What a taste sensation, monk monk!" class="wp-image-13373" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Marina surprised me by asking me for a squid! Was she looking for a new cousin? It took me way too long to track one town, but I did track one down eventually.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Marina: Oh! A squid!" class="wp-image-13374" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;She only rewarded me with 528 bells, but I guess it was okay. Because during my search, I also caught a few barred knifejaws and red snappers, which are worth a few thousand bells apiece.&lt;/p&gt;    &lt;p&gt;Later on, I went up to the Roost for K.K.&amp;#8217;s Saturday night show. I asked him for a random song, and he performed &amp;#8220;K.K. Country&amp;#8221; for me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="K.K.: All right, get ready to dig the riffs on this ditty: K.K. Country." class="wp-image-13375" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;Since the fish I caught earlier got me close to a new savings milestone, I gathered up a few loads of fruit to add to it. My balance has now reached 67 million bells.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;div class="wp-block-image"&gt; &lt;figure class="aligncenter size-full"&gt;&lt;img width="500" height="268" src="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/Array" alt="Your current balance is 67,000,000 bells." class="wp-image-13376" sizes="auto, (max-width: 500px) 100vw, 500px" /&gt;&lt;/figure&gt;&lt;/div&gt;   &lt;p&gt;See you next time!&lt;/p&gt; 	&lt;/div&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-content --&gt;  	 	&lt;footer class="entry-footer"&gt; 		&lt;span class="posted-on"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Posted on &lt;/span&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/2025/04/26/marinas-squid/" rel="bookmark"&gt;&lt;time class="entry-date published" datetime="2025-04-26T23:58:00-04:00"&gt;April 26, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;time class="updated" datetime="2025-04-27T00:46:34-04:00"&gt;April 27, 2025&lt;/time&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="byline"&gt;&lt;span class="screen-reader-text"&gt;Author &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class="author vcard"&gt;&lt;a class="url fn n" href="https://www.jvgs.net/accfblog/author/jvgsjeff/"&gt;Jeff&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;			&lt;/footer&gt;&lt;!-- .entry-footer --&gt;  &lt;/article&gt;</description>
